This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a method for online adaptation of neural network-based models. It also involves the use of filtering techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning. Additionally, the paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as behavior prediction of intelligent agents is a common problem in these fields. The use of dynamic multi-epoch update strategy may also suggest that the paper belongs to cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.SY (Systems and Control) as these fields often involve real-time adaptation of models.
